Flask + MongoDB Atlas Web Application (DevOps Assignment)

Project Overview

This project is a Flask-based web application integrated with MongoDB Atlas.
It includes a frontend form, backend API, Docker support, and cloud database integration.

Features
* Flask web server
* REST API (/api) returning JSON data
* HTML form with Bootstrap UI
* MongoDB Atlas cloud database integration
* Data insertion from frontend form
* Flash messages for success/failure

Tech Stack
* Python (Flask)
* MongoDB Atlas
* HTML + Bootstrap

Project Structure
flask-mongodb-app/
│
├── app.py
├── data.json
├── requirements.txt
├── Dockerfile
├── README.md
│
├── templates/
│   ├── index.html
│
└── static/

Setup Instructions
1. Clone repository
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd flask-mongodb-app

2. Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run application
python app.py / flask run --host=0.0.0.0 --port=5000

5. API Endpoint
http://<IP>:5000/api
